ray.surface

Class Surface

  • java.lang.Object
    • ray.surface.Surface
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Mesh, MeshTriangle, Sphere, Triangle

    public abstract class Surface
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract base class for all surfaces. Provides access for material and intersection uniformly for all surfaces. Note that this class should not contain a material pointer. Material pointers are left under the control of the implementation. This allows very lightweight surfaces, a good example are MeshTriangle which merely reference triangles in a TriangleMesh surface, to share a material pointer.
    Author:
    ags

      • intersect

        public abstract boolean intersect(IntersectionRecord outRecord,
                                  Ray ray)
        Tests this surface for intersection with ray. If an intersection is found record is filled out with the information about the intersection and the method returns true. It returns false otherwise and the information in outRecord is not modified.
        Parameters:
        outRecord - the output IntersectionRecord
        ray - the ray to intersect
        Returns:
        true if the surface intersects the ray
